@ocefpaf I didn't know about conda-lock. From what I can gather from the docs, it solves a slightly different problem. The point of conda-export is to create an environment spec file similar to `conda env export --from-history`, adding the packages that were installed separately with pip.

Of course, you are most welcome to use any of my code. But I should warn you that it's pretty naive, probably doesn't handle some tricky edge cases and it uses private `pip` API that can change at any moment. If you find a way to improve it, please ping me so I can incorporate those improvements into conda-export.

Thank you!

